OL,5,Crise
OL,7,F"People should stay at least 2.75
OL,8,Fmetres away from OLE at all times and
OL,9,Ftake extra care when carrying objects
OL,10,Fsuch as umbrellas, helium balloons and
OL,11,Ffishing rods."
OL,13,FThe introduction of Overhead Line
OL,14,FEquipment aims to provide more
OL,15,Fsustainable and efficient trains. But
OL,16,FTfW says the lines pose new dangers,
OL,17,Fmeaning the risks associated with anti-
OL,18,Fsocial behaviour have significantly
OL,19,Fincreased.
